description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity to provide a specialist role and move into an established post. We are seeking a highly motivated and skilled Maxillofacial Prosthetist/Reconstructive Scientist to join our busy and stimulating service as Principle/Service Deputy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Maxillofacial Prosthetics Service provides a comprehensive clinical and technical service for the whole of Dorset encompassing oncology, trauma, orthognathic surgery planning, facial and body prosthetics and implant rehabilitation work. We provide an on-call service to be available for traumatic emergencies and specialist case work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to the personal and professional development of our staff and the service is part of the South West Training Consortium for Healthcare Science, Scientific Training Programme with a current cohort of Trainee’s. In addition we have close links to the Distance and Full Time MSc courses at King’s College, London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a Maxillofacial Prosthetist/Reconstructive Scientist with excellent communication skills, you enjoy working under pressure, using your initiative and would like to contribute to the work of a busy unit we look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: if this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 08/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provisional interview date: 30/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information concerning the post and to arrange an informal visit please contact: Heidi Silk heidi.silk@uhd.nhs.uk and Mark Townend mark.townend@uhd.nhs.uk Telephone: 0300 0192148. Subject to applicable pandemic restrictions&lt;/p&gt;
